Another strategy we should agree on is how to distinguish the UI elements in writing. I would favor capitalizing just the first letter (even when they appear fully capitalized in the UI, for readability purposes), and enclosing the UI element string inside `**` chars. That is `*Option*` instead of `OPTIONS` as you proposed. 

On another hand I also like the `*Plugin name > Tab name*` convention for indicating the current position of the user in Kolibri, that is `*Coach > Groups*`, `*Learn > Recommended*`, `*Facility > Settings*`, `*Device > Info*` and so forth... 
